1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 8=

3
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:03,260
Coming.

4
00:02:04,580 --> 00:02:04,940
Mom.

5
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:08,780
He Han is inside talking to your dad.

6
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:10,260
When I got here,

7
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:11,740
your dad wouldn't open the door.

8
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:13,300
Good thing He Han showed up.

9
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:14,820
He's so thoughtful.

10
00:02:15,180 --> 00:02:16,970
He never forgets

11
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:17,980
our birthdays.

12
00:02:17,980 --> 00:02:19,511
Of course. What took you so long?

13
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:20,660
I've been talking to your dad.

14
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:21,660
I told you not to come.

15
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:22,340
Why are you here?

16
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:22,940
When did you say that?

17
00:02:22,940 --> 00:02:23,660
Yesterday.

18
00:02:23,980 --> 00:02:24,420
Did you?

19
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:26,020
Go home right now.

20
00:02:26,260 --> 00:02:27,940
Your mom asked me to stay for lunch.

21
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:29,933
Are you done talking?

22
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:30,980
If so, leave now.

23
00:02:30,980 --> 00:02:32,180
If not, you have five minutes.

24
00:02:32,580 --> 00:02:33,810
I'm here for your own good.

25
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:34,740
To lighten the mood.

26
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:36,140
Isn't it nice to get along?

27
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:38,020
That's only temporary.

28
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:39,180
The drama is coming.

29
00:02:39,540 --> 00:02:40,540
You're just in the way.

30
00:02:40,780 --> 00:02:42,020
How am I in the way?

31
00:02:42,020 --> 00:02:43,060
- Getting along...
- Mom.

32
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,420
Something came up for He Han.

33
00:02:44,420 --> 00:02:45,580
- He has to leave.
- I'm fine, Mrs. Lin.

34
00:02:45,580 --> 00:02:46,820
Aren't you staying for lunch?

35
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:48,300
- Yeah, just a few bites.
- Talk to him later.

36
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:49,320
Don't give him an attitude.

37
00:02:49,330 --> 00:02:50,500
I have to take your mom home.

38
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,880
- I can take you home.
- The food is ready.

39
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:52,780
- Food is ready.
- Food is ready. Come on.

40
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:53,580
Okay, Mrs. Lin.

41
00:02:53,580 --> 00:02:54,260
Just a few bites.

42
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:55,288
Lunch's ready, Mr. Lin.

43
00:02:55,580 --> 00:02:56,580
You'll hold things up.

44
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,100
They'll be waiting for you.

45
00:02:58,180 --> 00:02:59,180
Let them wait.

46
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:02,060
Drink less alcohol.

47
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:03,540
Have some juice.

48
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:03,900
Okay.

49
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:06,020
Family together,

50
00:03:06,340 --> 00:03:08,060
healthy and happy.

51
00:03:08,260 --> 00:03:08,980
Isn't it great?

52
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:09,740
Come on.

53
00:03:09,740 --> 00:03:11,180
I said keep it simple,

54
00:03:11,180 --> 00:03:12,220
but you made a feast again.

55
00:03:12,666 --> 00:03:14,740
You're tired cooking it,
and we're tired eating it.

56
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:16,780
Can't you ever just relax?

57
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:18,020
It's a birthday.

58
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:19,780
You're like this birthday or not.

59
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:21,220
Dad.

60
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:22,300
Okay.

61
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:23,540
You and Mom

62
00:03:23,540 --> 00:03:25,300
don't eat together every day, right?

63
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:26,980
If you see something you like,

64
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:27,900
eat more.

65
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:29,460
If not, don't eat it.

66
00:03:30,020 --> 00:03:30,660
Put up with it.

67
00:03:31,220 --> 00:03:33,140
I worked hard to make extra dishes

68
00:03:33,580 --> 00:03:34,940
so we could finally

69
00:03:34,940 --> 00:03:36,900
have a nice family dinner

70
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:37,700
and be happy.

71
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:39,780
Why should he have to "put up with it"?

72
00:03:41,540 --> 00:03:42,100
Come on, eat.

73
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:43,860
I'll say it again.

74
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:46,220
Just because you work hard,

75
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:47,660
doesn't mean we'll be happy.

76
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:54,620
You should go.

77
00:03:56,380 --> 00:03:57,730
If we really start fighting,

78
00:03:57,730 --> 00:03:58,700
lunch will be ruined.

79
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:01,180
This isn't fighting.

80
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:02,940
We're just expressing opinions. Right?

81
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:04,580
This is great. I love this.

82
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:05,620
Family together,

83
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:06,820
talking things out.

84
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:08,100
It's lively and fun.

85
00:04:08,380 --> 00:04:09,060
Mr. Lin, come on.

86
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:09,940
Cheers.

87
00:04:10,060 --> 00:04:11,500
Happy birthday. To your health.

88
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:13,220
And thanks for fixing my erhu.

89
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:14,780
What erhu?

90
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:15,700
A new hobby.

91
00:04:16,380 --> 00:04:18,260
He Han appreciates our folk music.

92
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:20,380
That erhu is a good one.

93
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:22,020
The resonator was cracked.

94
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,340
Fixing it was no big deal.

95
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:24,300
Thank you.

96
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,220
Good thing He Han came today. Here.

97
00:04:27,660 --> 00:04:28,180
Eat up.

98
00:04:28,266 --> 00:04:29,360
- Thanks.
- Have some soup.

99
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:30,380
Mom, let him eat

100
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:31,300
what he wants.

101
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,977
Mrs. Lin, I'll eat whatever you give me.

102
00:04:33,260 --> 00:04:34,100
She's stubborn,

103
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:35,660
and has a sharp tongue.

104
00:04:35,900 --> 00:04:36,780
Be patient with her.

105
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:38,820
Get married soon.

106
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:39,460
No problem.

107
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:41,140
We broke up ages ago.

108
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:42,300
I'm not marrying him.

109
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,980
Fighting out of spite

110
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:45,220
is perfectly normal.

111
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:46,420
Aren't you fine now?

112
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:46,900
Look.

113
00:04:47,140 --> 00:04:49,244
He Han is sitting
right here and eating with us.

114
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:50,940
Please talk some sense into her.

115
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,460
If things don't work out

116
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:53,180
with her boyfriend,

117
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:54,500
she can come back to me anytime.

118
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:55,700
Do I have a boyfriend?

119
00:04:55,820 --> 00:04:56,620
Can you tell me?

120
00:04:57,066 --> 00:04:58,850
Could you please stop making things up?

121
00:04:58,850 --> 00:04:59,300
He Han.

122
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,900
You shouldn't marry Zhanqiao.

123
00:05:02,377 --> 00:05:03,511
She's not worthy of you.

124
00:05:04,540 --> 00:05:05,220
As a father,

125
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:06,900
I shouldn't say this.

126
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:09,220
But as your friend,

127
00:05:09,340 --> 00:05:10,020
your confidant,

128
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:11,900
I have to be honest.

129
00:05:12,533 --> 00:05:13,340
My dad makes a good point.

130
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:14,100
I don't mind that.

131
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:18,060
This new boyfriend He Han mentioned...

132
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:19,140
What does he do?

133
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:21,260
An up-and-coming young author.

134
00:05:21,377 --> 00:05:22,500
His writing is mediocre.

135
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:23,980
But he is quite handsome.

136
00:05:24,511 --> 00:05:26,100
He's probably relying on Lin Zhanqiao

137
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,020
to top the charts.

138
00:05:29,380 --> 00:05:30,980
Don't be fooled.

139
00:05:30,980 --> 00:05:32,220
He might just be using you.

140
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:33,580
He has natural talent.

141
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:35,220
He was born to write.

142
00:05:36,288 --> 00:05:37,620
With just a few casual updates,

143
00:05:38,020 --> 00:05:38,700
he can instantly

144
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:39,900
dominate the top of the charts.

145
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:45,980
Mom, let me tell you,

146
00:05:46,622 --> 00:05:48,300
I've been in this industry a long time.

147
00:05:48,300 --> 00:05:49,820
A naturally gifted writer like him

148
00:05:50,260 --> 00:05:51,180
is one of a kind.

149
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:52,740
Absolutely unique.

150
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:54,260
Top of the charts?

151
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:56,060
Does he write better than He Han?

152
00:05:56,088 --> 00:05:57,210
That's impossible, Mr. Lin.

153
00:05:57,210 --> 00:05:58,290
I haven't been writing lately.

154
00:05:58,290 --> 00:05:58,890
I'm on hiatus.

155
00:05:59,088 --> 00:06:00,288
Good thing you're on hiatus.

156
00:06:00,420 --> 00:06:01,900
Otherwise, getting crushed by a rookie

157
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:02,660
would be

158
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:04,340
humiliating.

159
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:06,100
Being a good writer

160
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:08,580
doesn't make him a good boyfriend.

161
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:09,660
Who doesn't love a genius?

162
00:06:09,755 --> 00:06:11,355
Beauty is in the eye of the beholder.

163
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:13,050
What's his name?

164
00:06:13,050 --> 00:06:13,540
Gu Yan.

165
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:14,660
Gu Yan?

166
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:16,290
That's not a good name.

167
00:06:16,290 --> 00:06:16,780
Right?

168
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:19,088
Mr. Lin, look at this.

169
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:20,860
Are you done?

170
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:25,260
Let me see, too.

171
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,177
What does he look like?

172
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:28,460
Look.

173
00:06:29,711 --> 00:06:30,980
Everyone is getting along.

174
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:31,540
Like this.

175
00:06:36,180 --> 00:06:37,300
What were you thinking?

176
00:06:37,820 --> 00:06:39,020
My new boyfriend?

177
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,700
Gu Yan is my new author.

178
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:42,540
We have a strictly
professional relationship.

179
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,060
You think everyone is like you?

180
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:45,020
What did I do?

181
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:46,660
You mean...

182
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,380
You've only known
Dai Shan for a few days.

183
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,820
And you're flirting with her

184
00:06:50,820 --> 00:06:52,060
before you even started working!

185
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:54,060
Dipping your pen
in the company ink, huh?

186
00:06:54,940 --> 00:06:55,460
Jealous?

187
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:57,260
I'm not jealous!

188
00:06:57,700 --> 00:06:59,260
I just despise your character.

189
00:06:59,940 --> 00:07:00,500
Dai Shan

190
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,460
is a bit older than me.

191
00:07:01,460 --> 00:07:02,700
She is thoughtful.

192
00:07:03,020 --> 00:07:03,740
She can solve

193
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:05,260
a problem so calmly.

194
00:07:05,380 --> 00:07:06,700
Girls my age would rather

195
00:07:07,020 --> 00:07:08,488
stick together 24/7.

196
00:07:08,555 --> 00:07:10,420
They throw tantrums
over every little thing.

197
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:11,700
They threaten
to break up with me.

198
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:12,420
First of all.

199
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,500
I only spent every day with you

200
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:15,940
because of work.

201
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:16,500
Second.

202
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:17,900
Those "little things"

203
00:07:18,060 --> 00:07:19,888
were the straw
that broke the camel's back.

204
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,688
I put up with you over and over again.

205
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:23,180
Third.

206
00:07:23,733 --> 00:07:24,740
Even though we used to

207
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:26,260
break up and get back together a lot,

208
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:27,888
that was because
I had feelings for you.

209
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:28,540
But this time,

210
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:29,820
we broke up for good.

211
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:31,140
Why so defensive?

212
00:07:31,260 --> 00:07:32,420
I was talking about Mimi.

213
00:07:34,980 --> 00:07:35,740
I know.

214
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:37,980
Our issues weren't entirely your fault.

215
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:38,740
I had my flaws, too.

216
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:40,300
Not entirely my fault?

217
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:41,140
It was 50/50.

218
00:07:47,020 --> 00:07:48,300
Thank you for today.

219
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:50,180
I appreciate your kindness.

220
00:07:50,460 --> 00:07:52,140
But you keep coming after we broke up.

221
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:53,530
I hate that.

222
00:07:53,530 --> 00:07:55,130
I always have a reason for finding you.

223
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:56,820
Even though we broke up,
if I see an issue,

224
00:07:56,820 --> 00:07:57,900
I still have a responsibility

225
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:58,540
to warn you.

226
00:07:58,740 --> 00:07:59,660
Just like today.

227
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:00,860
Right? It's no big deal.

228
00:08:00,860 --> 00:08:01,780
Thank you for that.

229
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:03,460
Never do it again.

230
00:08:03,740 --> 00:08:04,340
Lin Zhanqiao.

231
00:08:04,340 --> 00:08:06,377
Do we have some deep-seated
hatred for each other?

232
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:08,540
Is there a need to cut each other off?

233
00:08:10,220 --> 00:08:11,140
Unless you admit

234
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:13,020
you can't let me go.

235
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,660
Seeing me still messes
with your emotions.

236
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:15,460
I admit it.

237
00:08:15,780 --> 00:08:16,900
I still care about you a lot.

238
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:18,540
You already have a girlfriend.

239
00:08:18,688 --> 00:08:20,180
I'm looking for a new boyfriend too.

240
00:08:20,420 --> 00:08:21,940
We should stop talking about this.

241
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:23,940
Do you really believe
I'm dating Dai Shan?

242
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:24,820
It's all fake.

243
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:26,200
That was just to deal with Mimi.

244
00:08:26,580 --> 00:08:27,660
So you and Mimi were real?

245
00:08:28,020 --> 00:08:28,820
I never touched her.

246
00:08:37,740 --> 00:08:38,500
Why are you here?

247
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:40,620
To pick you up.

248
00:08:40,777 --> 00:08:41,911
Heading back to the office?

249
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:42,740
I'll take a cab.

250
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,020
Don't look
for a new boyfriend online.

251
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:45,900
Too many scammers.

252
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:01,540
You're that worried?

253
00:09:01,822 --> 00:09:03,260
You came all the way to pick me up.

254
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:05,860
What if you two got back together?

255
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:07,780
I can lose a boyfriend.

256
00:09:08,260 --> 00:09:09,380
But I can't afford to lose

257
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:10,620
a star author.

258
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:12,900
You underestimate yourself.

259
00:09:13,180 --> 00:09:14,500
I bought this car

260
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,580
just to show how much I value you.

261
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:18,780
It doesn't matter if I look bad.

262
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:20,340
But you need to look good, right?

263
00:09:20,940 --> 00:09:21,620
Thanks, boss.

264
00:09:24,260 --> 00:09:26,700
Lin Zhanqiao got
Zhiyuan's venture capital.

265
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:27,740
Did you know?

266
00:09:28,540 --> 00:09:29,180
Good for her.

267
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:31,860
With just one Gu Yan.

268
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:32,900
What does that tell you?

269
00:09:33,377 --> 00:09:34,700
That Gu Yan is a heavy hitter.

270
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:37,610
It shows that this money

271
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:38,850
isn't for Gu Yan.

272
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:40,260
It's for Lin Zhanqiao.

273
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:42,010
By producing a Gu Yan,

274
00:09:42,010 --> 00:09:43,780
she proved her own capability.

275
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:45,380
She doesn't rely on you,

276
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:47,740
He Han, to make a career.

277
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:50,740
On the contrary,

278
00:09:51,066 --> 00:09:52,740
you go on hiatus right
after a breakup.

279
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:54,100
People are saying that

280
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,820
without Lin Zhanqiao,

281
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,500
you can't write a single thing.

282
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,940
So we need to prove ourselves.

283
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,060
On your first day back,

284
00:10:02,860 --> 00:10:03,620
we need a big win.

285
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,780
Okay. Don't worry.

286
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:07,460
Revise it.

287
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:08,200
What is this?

288
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:13,980
Who made these annotations?

289
00:10:14,980 --> 00:10:16,860
The AI evaluation system I'm using.

290
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:21,140
Writing a novel based on AI evaluation?

291
00:10:23,340 --> 00:10:24,460
Don't underestimate it.

292
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:26,500
The developers used

293
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:29,010
massive amounts of fiction
and reader feedback.

294
00:10:29,010 --> 00:10:30,980
It's proven to predict reader tastes...

295
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:32,780
A Lotus is a Lotus.

296
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:35,180
It wasn't created

297
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:36,500
just by studying

298
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:37,620
masses of car design data.

299
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,460
You don't have to agree with it,

300
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,300
but you shouldn't ignore it.

301
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:51,260
Hi, Ms. Lin.

302
00:10:51,740 --> 00:10:52,100
Ms. Lin.

303
00:10:56,940 --> 00:10:57,300
Ms. Lin.

304
00:10:57,622 --> 00:10:58,420
You didn't go back?

305
00:10:59,022 --> 00:11:00,200
Where are you staying?

306
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:01,780
At a friend's place.

307
00:11:02,740 --> 00:11:04,380
It isn't a long-term solution.

308
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:05,860
No.

309
00:11:06,460 --> 00:11:08,940
Ms. Lin, life has
no long-term solutions.

310
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:10,380
Only long-term wandering.

311
00:11:12,780 --> 00:11:14,260
He Han's sentimental lines

312
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:15,300
are nice to read.

313
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:16,980
Using them to guide your life

314
00:11:17,180 --> 00:11:17,860
is meaningless.

315
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:20,580
While you're "wandering,"

316
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:22,340
others are driving luxury cars.

317
00:11:28,580 --> 00:11:30,020
By the way, He Han asked

318
00:11:30,020 --> 00:11:30,980
if you were here yet.

319
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:32,580
He has something to drop off.

320
00:11:34,377 --> 00:11:35,420
Tell him not to bother.

321
00:11:35,533 --> 00:11:36,866
I don't need anything from him.

322
00:11:41,955 --> 00:11:43,555
What are you waiting for? Go.

323
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:48,620
Milk tea is on me today.

324
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:50,900
Once the investment contract is signed,

325
00:11:51,022 --> 00:11:52,340
we'll celebrate with champagne.

326
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:52,940
Thanks!

327
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:53,380
Thank you!

328
00:11:53,380 --> 00:11:54,260
Thanks, Ms. Lin.

329
00:11:54,460 --> 00:11:55,260
You're the best.

330
00:11:56,980 --> 00:11:57,420
Thanks.

331
00:11:58,980 --> 00:11:59,820
The financial strain

332
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:01,780
and resignations

333
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:03,900
have made recent days

334
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,580
incredibly tough

335
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:06,620
for all of us.

336
00:12:08,020 --> 00:12:09,460
We barely had the budget

337
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:10,860
to sign new authors.

338
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:14,100
But thankfully,

339
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:16,580
things are about to change.

340
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:19,100
So please, get ready to kick off

341
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:20,220
our next phase of work.

342
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:20,700
Okay.

343
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:23,700
Gu Yan is our star right now.

344
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,940
But to be safe,

345
00:12:26,111 --> 00:12:27,330
we shouldn't put all our eggs

346
00:12:27,330 --> 00:12:28,980
in one basket.

347
00:12:29,900 --> 00:12:32,140
Who knows if he'll turn
into another He Han?

348
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:36,140
Lawyer Bei has included strict clauses

349
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,660
in Gu Yan's contract.

350
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:39,622
Ms. Lin, don't you think
our line of work

351
00:12:39,666 --> 00:12:41,311
is a bit different from others?

352
00:12:41,620 --> 00:12:42,980
Just suppose

353
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:45,020
he starts slacking off
or writing garbage.

354
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:45,460
Then what?

355
00:12:45,460 --> 00:12:47,560
Authors on the rise don't
have the luxury to slack off.

356
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:48,850
And once they're past that stage?

357
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:51,060
We make sure we always
have new rising stars.

358
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:57,244
Mantou will handle the coordination.

359
00:12:58,060 --> 00:12:59,020
Fragile will keep an eye

360
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:00,022
on the big-name authors.

361
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,180
Scouting for new talent

362
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:02,511
will be Naobaijin's job.

363
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:03,740
It might be too much for her.

364
00:13:04,822 --> 00:13:06,977
Zhangzhu, you always
wanted to be an editor.

365
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:08,100
Why not start now?

366
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,577
Learn the ropes from Naobaijin.

367
00:13:10,377 --> 00:13:11,620
That's amazing! So that means

368
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:13,020
I can finally work as an editor

369
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:14,580
and manage my own authors?

370
00:13:15,820 --> 00:13:17,500
Thank you for trusting me with this.

371
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:18,620
You've got this. Work hard!

372
00:13:18,620 --> 00:13:19,820
Good luck! You can do it!

373
00:13:19,820 --> 00:13:21,800
(Still want the lore book?)
Scouting for rookies is a grind.

374
00:13:22,380 --> 00:13:23,780
Anyway, welcome to the game.

375
00:13:24,060 --> 00:13:25,260
Thank you! Thank you!

376
00:13:28,660 --> 00:13:31,060
♪Please don't let me sense it♪

377
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,420
♪I'm only interested in what's in sight♪

378
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:35,860
♪Please don't call my name♪

379
00:13:35,860 --> 00:13:38,220
♪I'm still finding
my place in the crowd♪

380
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:40,700
♪Please don't give me an address♪

381
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:43,140
♪Let my feet take me where they will♪

382
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:52,220
Come on in.

383
00:13:53,340 --> 00:13:54,140
I'll stay out here.

384
00:13:54,220 --> 00:13:55,180
Just bring it out to me.

385
00:13:55,420 --> 00:13:56,500
What are you so afraid of?

386
00:13:56,660 --> 00:13:58,100
No one's inside, I promise.

387
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,220
No men or women.

388
00:14:04,111 --> 00:14:06,100
I offered to bring it to you,
but you refused.

389
00:14:06,340 --> 00:14:07,700
Now you had to come here for it.

390
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:10,900
Come in for some tea

391
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:11,740
and thank me.

392
00:14:12,180 --> 00:14:13,580
It wasn't easy finding this for you.

393
00:14:14,860 --> 00:14:15,340
Thanks.

394
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,020
At the end of the chapter,

395
00:14:17,660 --> 00:14:18,820
I'll have Gu Yan write a note

396
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,800
thanking you
for providing the lore book.

397
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:22,380
You...

398
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:26,220
Anything else?

399
00:14:26,820 --> 00:14:27,780
Won't you open it?

400
00:14:28,060 --> 00:14:28,940
When I get back.

401
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:30,460
I'll walk you back, then.

402
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:37,660
Won't you read it?

403
00:14:38,380 --> 00:14:39,180
Just one look.

404
00:14:39,180 --> 00:14:40,180
Just a glimpse is fine.

405
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:40,780
It's done

406
00:14:41,660 --> 00:14:42,220
in no time.

407
00:14:44,020 --> 00:14:44,660
Go on.

408
00:14:44,780 --> 00:14:46,220
I worked so hard

409
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:46,900
to get this.

410
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:48,220
What's wrong with it?

411
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:49,420
Why are you following me?

412
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,100
You'd know if you looked at it.

413
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:54,140
Still no?

414
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:54,860
Impressive.

415
00:14:55,180 --> 00:14:55,540
Fine.

416
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:03,980
I have other things
to take care of.

417
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:04,780
Thank you.

418
00:15:05,180 --> 00:15:06,220
I know what's inside.

419
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:07,380
Thank me after you look.

420
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:08,100
Then, I'll go.

421
00:15:09,980 --> 00:15:10,460
Mr. He...

422
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:12,540
For real?

423
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:13,688
It'll only take a minute.

424
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,488
I thought this was gone.

425
00:15:30,180 --> 00:15:30,980
Fine, I've looked.

426
00:15:31,860 --> 00:15:32,380
Leave now.

427
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:41,380
Wait.

428
00:15:52,780 --> 00:15:54,140
You said we couldn't enter Guazhou.

429
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:55,540
You insisted on it.

430
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:06,740
Is this a new map you made?

431
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:08,260
Who else?

432
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:10,955
But you said
that entering Guazhou would ruin

433
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:12,220
the rest of the story.

434
00:16:13,660 --> 00:16:14,620
How did you get the map?

435
00:16:14,780 --> 00:16:16,780
I meant it was a bad idea for Gu Yan.

436
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:19,020
If I write it,
I can definitely find a way.

437
00:16:19,860 --> 00:16:20,900
It's interesting, right?

438
00:16:21,380 --> 00:16:22,500
I marked the stages for you.

439
00:16:22,580 --> 00:16:23,220
I see that.

440
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:29,740
So...

441
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:32,622
Don't you think you should thank me?

442
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:40,155
I honestly didn't expect you

443
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:43,100
to help out with Gu Yan's story.

444
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:44,940
I've got nothing but time.

445
00:16:45,740 --> 00:16:46,460
Sure, I could be

446
00:16:46,460 --> 00:16:47,644
doing plenty of other things,

447
00:16:47,660 --> 00:16:48,340
but I figured

448
00:16:48,660 --> 00:16:50,060
the bond always remains.

449
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:52,020
Besides, your parents
were always good to me.

450
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:53,511
And I suppose it's possible

451
00:16:53,555 --> 00:16:55,100
I wasted a bit of your youth.

452
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:56,666
But, you have to
take some blame too.

453
00:16:56,755 --> 00:16:57,533
Either way,

454
00:16:57,620 --> 00:16:58,460
it was no trouble.

455
00:16:58,860 --> 00:16:59,700
I'm happy to help.

456
00:17:00,444 --> 00:17:06,155
♪If the sky and the sea
turned upside down♪

457
00:17:07,580 --> 00:17:08,220
Thank you.

458
00:17:12,022 --> 00:17:12,977
You're welcome.

459
00:17:17,460 --> 00:17:18,490
Are you moved?

460
00:17:18,490 --> 00:17:20,620
Do you regret being
so mean and cold to me earlier?

461
00:17:20,620 --> 00:17:21,660
What are you really after?

462
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:24,300
"Drunk Old Friend"

463
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,540
is a story we wrote together.

464
00:17:26,822 --> 00:17:28,622
Even if you're giving it to Gu Yan,

465
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:30,460
I don't want to see it become a mess.

466
00:17:30,460 --> 00:17:32,460
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

467
00:17:32,460 --> 00:17:34,222
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

468
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:35,340
Anything else?

469
00:17:35,340 --> 00:17:36,620
Let him realize his limits.

470
00:17:37,066 --> 00:17:38,420
Not every hill can be overcome.

471
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,100
And?

472
00:17:39,888 --> 00:17:43,666
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

473
00:17:44,822 --> 00:17:48,511
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

474
00:17:48,740 --> 00:17:49,980
I gave him such a great story,

475
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:52,700
a perfect way to break the deadlock,

476
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,100
and even you,

477
00:17:55,020 --> 00:17:56,860
a brilliant editor.

478
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:00,660
If he can't write it well,

479
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:03,540
won't you be disappointed?

480
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:14,660
Just ask me anything.

481
00:18:14,820 --> 00:18:16,420
I'll tell you everything I know.

482
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,949
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

483
00:18:24,950 --> 00:18:26,729
♪Running in opposite ways♪

484
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:29,333
♪Searching all along the way♪

485
00:18:31,580 --> 00:18:33,140
(He Han is just like he used to be.)

486
00:18:34,088 --> 00:18:36,022
(One moment
he's dousing me with ice water,)

487
00:18:37,180 --> 00:18:38,940
(the next,
he's making my heart bloom.)

488
00:18:41,711 --> 00:18:42,660
(After the breakup,)

489
00:18:43,444 --> 00:18:44,900
(I'm learning to desensitize.)

490
00:18:45,066 --> 00:18:47,439
♪In another time and space♪

491
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:50,800
♪We'll stay and walk together
till we grow old♪

492
00:18:50,860 --> 00:18:52,740
(Guazhou)

493
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:53,980
(Use jade to open the door.)

494
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:55,860
(Break the seal.)

495
00:18:55,860 --> 00:18:58,740
(Search for Buddhist artifacts.)

496
00:19:11,622 --> 00:19:12,755
What are you doing?

497
00:19:14,740 --> 00:19:15,620
Mr. He Han.

498
00:19:16,580 --> 00:19:17,620
Using the office as a dorm?

499
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,580
Is this place even livable?

500
00:19:19,580 --> 00:19:20,340
It's so unsafe.

501
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:22,060
What if something falls and hits you?

502
00:19:22,780 --> 00:19:23,900
There is no ventilation.

503
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:25,340
You're breathing in all this dust.

504
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:29,060
I...

505
00:19:29,820 --> 00:19:30,300
just...

506
00:19:30,940 --> 00:19:32,180
It's only for a few days.

507
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:34,340
Once I find a roommate,

508
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:35,260
I'll move out.

509
00:19:37,622 --> 00:19:39,300
Pack your things and come with me.

510
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:40,820
What?

511
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:42,088
You need a place to stay.

512
00:19:42,420 --> 00:19:43,460
Just stay at my place.

513
00:19:43,780 --> 00:19:45,300
It's the least I can do for a fan.

514
00:19:45,940 --> 00:19:47,620
No, no. That's not right.

515
00:19:48,540 --> 00:19:49,460
You stay at a hotel.

516
00:19:50,820 --> 00:19:52,340
You're at a hotel...

517
00:19:52,780 --> 00:19:54,140
How can I go there with you?

518
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:56,100
No, this is totally inappropriate.

519
00:19:56,780 --> 00:19:57,060
I...

520
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,220
That place isn't right for me.

521
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:02,020
"That place"?

522
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:03,980
What are you thinking?

523
00:20:04,380 --> 00:20:05,460
You read too many novels?

524
00:20:05,820 --> 00:20:07,420
Do you think I'm some kind of creep?

525
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:09,380
Sure, I like pretty girls.

526
00:20:09,380 --> 00:20:10,660
That's because I'm a normal man.

527
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:11,860
It doesn't mean I'm a pervert.

528
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:13,740
I'm almost your father's age.

529
00:20:13,977 --> 00:20:16,060
Though I guess
that doesn't mean much these days.

530
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:17,860
Plenty of creeps
are older than your dad.

531
00:20:17,955 --> 00:20:19,577
- Maybe even your own dad...
- No, no!

532
00:20:19,644 --> 00:20:21,180
Mr. He Han, you're my idol.

533
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:24,340
How could I ever think you were...

534
00:20:25,620 --> 00:20:26,220
A creep?

535
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:28,980
Look, that hotel room

536
00:20:29,420 --> 00:20:30,700
is expensive. I can't afford it.

537
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:31,900
I don't want
to ask my dad for money.

538
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:33,420
Is that all?
That's not a problem.

539
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:34,980
I'm a VIP there.

540
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:36,300
I have plenty of points saved up.

541
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:37,600
I can use those points.

542
00:20:39,060 --> 00:20:40,220
If it makes you feel better,

543
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:41,930
pay me what a hostel costs.

544
00:20:41,930 --> 00:20:43,060
How about thirty yuan a day?

545
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:45,220
Thirty yuan?

546
00:20:45,580 --> 00:20:46,220
Fine, twenty?

547
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:46,700
No.

548
00:20:47,260 --> 00:20:48,460
Thirty yuan is way too little.

549
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:50,500
It's fine.
It's not like you're making a fortune.

550
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:52,290
Enough, it's settled.

551
00:20:52,290 --> 00:20:53,500
Leave that junk behind.

552
00:20:56,780 --> 00:20:58,770
Come on. You just said I was your idol.

553
00:20:58,770 --> 00:20:59,980
Will you listen to your idol?

554
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,711
Stop stalling and let's go.

555
00:21:17,940 --> 00:21:18,620
You'll stay here.

556
00:21:19,660 --> 00:21:20,688
I'm right next door.

557
00:21:22,020 --> 00:21:24,340
Do you usually write in your room,

558
00:21:24,340 --> 00:21:25,500
or at the café downstairs?

559
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:27,180
Depends on my mood.

560
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:28,500
I'm on a break anyway.

561
00:21:29,860 --> 00:21:30,780
If you need anything,

562
00:21:30,860 --> 00:21:31,860
just call the front desk.

563
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:33,180
Thirty yuan a day.

564
00:21:33,260 --> 00:21:34,540
Just wire it to me every Monday.

565
00:21:35,644 --> 00:21:36,300
Get some rest.

566
00:21:36,780 --> 00:21:37,180
Okay.

567
00:21:40,780 --> 00:21:41,460
One more thing.

568
00:21:44,377 --> 00:21:46,377
Don't tell your boss
you're staying here.

569
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:48,940
Okay.

570
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:52,660
Thank you, Mr. He Han.

571
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:00,380
(Transferring funds to
"Great He Han")

572
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:11,700
Are you Ms. Zhou?

573
00:22:12,220 --> 00:22:12,540
Yes.

574
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:13,244
Delivery for you.

575
00:22:13,980 --> 00:22:14,460
Thank you.

576
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:47,260
(As you grow stronger,
the past will seem smaller.)

577
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:50,340
(As you grow stronger,
the past will seem smaller.)

578
00:24:06,020 --> 00:24:07,822
Hey, just got off work?

579
00:24:09,860 --> 00:24:10,460
I'm so sorry

580
00:24:10,460 --> 00:24:11,690
you have to see the house now.

581
00:24:11,690 --> 00:24:12,488
Take your time.

582
00:24:13,140 --> 00:24:13,580
No worries.

583
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:15,100
Look, young lady.

584
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:16,620
You know

585
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:18,222
the market is rough right now.

586
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:21,300
Normally, if you weren't in a rush,

587
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:23,260
I wouldn't suggest selling yet.

588
00:24:24,500 --> 00:24:25,355
It's an emergency.

589
00:24:27,020 --> 00:24:28,066
If you're in a rush,

590
00:24:28,222 --> 00:24:29,660
you're not going to get top money.

591
00:24:31,140 --> 00:24:32,980
I need at least seven million.

592
00:24:34,580 --> 00:24:35,940
With this interior?

593
00:24:36,377 --> 00:24:37,622
I think 6.3 million is fine.

594
00:24:37,777 --> 00:24:38,844
If we wait a bit,

595
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:39,980
it might be possible.

596
00:24:40,266 --> 00:24:40,933
I can't wait.

597
00:24:42,300 --> 00:24:43,500
How about a month?

598
00:24:44,260 --> 00:24:44,820
A week.

599
00:24:46,060 --> 00:24:46,820
Impossible.

600
00:24:50,580 --> 00:24:51,460
Seven million net.

601
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:52,780
We split the extra 60/40.

602
00:25:01,020 --> 00:25:01,820
So, 6.3 million?

603
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:03,780
I could try to push for that.

604
00:25:04,460 --> 00:25:04,940
Well?

605
00:25:12,740 --> 00:25:13,980
Let me think about it.

606
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:16,020
Sure. Go ahead and eat.

607
00:25:16,460 --> 00:25:17,580
Call me when you've decided.

608
00:25:18,140 --> 00:25:18,620
Take care.

609
00:25:18,777 --> 00:25:19,711
I'll head out then.

610
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:39,740
(7:42 PM, Zhao Lanxin:
Are you free tonight?)

611
00:25:54,100 --> 00:25:54,780
Why are you here?

612
00:25:55,660 --> 00:25:57,060
You never replied to my text.

613
00:25:58,820 --> 00:26:00,420
I was worried about you after today.

614
00:26:01,740 --> 00:26:02,260
Come on in.

615
00:26:14,380 --> 00:26:15,740
You're an independent,

616
00:26:15,940 --> 00:26:16,940
successful adult now.

617
00:26:18,940 --> 00:26:19,900
You're not

618
00:26:21,460 --> 00:26:22,540
that helpless child

619
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:23,940
under her thumb anymore.

620
00:26:26,660 --> 00:26:28,260
She doesn't have power over you now.

621
00:26:30,220 --> 00:26:31,420
Whatever you love,

622
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,088
it's okay to love it.

623
00:26:47,020 --> 00:26:48,500
This is your favorite color.

624
00:26:50,140 --> 00:26:51,740
You deserve the most beautiful colors,

625
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:54,100
the best clothes,

626
00:26:55,260 --> 00:26:55,820
and jewelry.

627
00:26:57,140 --> 00:26:57,580
All of it.

628
00:27:00,100 --> 00:27:00,740
You deserve

629
00:27:02,111 --> 00:27:03,800
to be more beautiful than anyone.

630
00:27:12,620 --> 00:27:13,620
Can you paint nails?

631
00:27:14,260 --> 00:27:14,820
Not really.

632
00:27:17,020 --> 00:27:18,340
But I'm willing to try for you.

633
00:28:11,700 --> 00:28:12,740
(Guazhou)

634
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:14,460
(Underground Black Market)

635
00:28:14,460 --> 00:28:15,500
(The Flaming Arena)

636
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,300
What do you think?

637
00:28:18,220 --> 00:28:19,180
It looks really useful.

638
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:22,100
But He Han wrote this.

639
00:28:22,540 --> 00:28:23,260
Can I use it?

640
00:28:23,580 --> 00:28:24,380
Of course.

641
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:26,022
Not only can you use it,

642
00:28:26,340 --> 00:28:27,860
you should write down any questions

643
00:28:27,860 --> 00:28:29,500
you have about the plot.

644
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:31,380
I'll take them to him for a Q&A session.

645
00:28:31,780 --> 00:28:32,700
Is he joking?

646
00:28:33,700 --> 00:28:34,380
He said that,

647
00:28:34,555 --> 00:28:35,844
so I take it seriously.

648
00:28:39,980 --> 00:28:40,460
Forget it.

649
00:28:41,740 --> 00:28:42,660
I'm not him.

650
00:28:43,420 --> 00:28:44,500
If I write his story,

651
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:46,140
it has to be done my way.

652
00:28:47,580 --> 00:28:48,340
Keep an open mind.

653
00:28:48,755 --> 00:28:50,060
Yours or his, it doesn't matter.

654
00:28:50,300 --> 00:28:51,340
Just go with the best idea.

655
00:28:53,020 --> 00:28:55,500
What if he's leading me
in the wrong direction?

656
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:56,020
What, then?

657
00:28:56,140 --> 00:28:56,580
He won't.

658
00:28:57,260 --> 00:28:58,540
He's too proud for that.

659
00:28:58,540 --> 00:28:59,860
He doesn't play petty games.

660
00:29:01,060 --> 00:29:02,380
What he really wants is

661
00:29:02,660 --> 00:29:04,580
to hand you the blueprint,

662
00:29:04,740 --> 00:29:06,755
and still have
the readers prefer him over you.

663
00:29:10,180 --> 00:29:10,900
You don't buy it.

664
00:29:16,540 --> 00:29:16,900
Fine.

665
00:29:17,540 --> 00:29:18,380
I'll finish eating

666
00:29:18,380 --> 00:29:19,420
and write some questions.

667
00:29:29,860 --> 00:29:30,540
Needed upstairs?

668
00:29:31,620 --> 00:29:33,140
I said I'm not doing the raid.

669
00:29:36,580 --> 00:29:38,570
Everyone, get in position!

670
00:29:38,570 --> 00:29:39,940
Why are you just standing there?

671
00:29:40,700 --> 00:29:42,540
Team 1 healers, hurry up!

672
00:29:42,540 --> 00:29:44,260
Don't just stand there!
Group up and push!

673
00:29:44,260 --> 00:29:45,700
Throw your items right at the start!

674
00:29:45,780 --> 00:29:46,860
Don't just charge in alone.

675
00:29:46,860 --> 00:29:48,060
Is this your first day playing?

676
00:29:48,060 --> 00:29:48,740
Tell me!

677
00:29:49,540 --> 00:29:51,020
Hurry up, Team 1! Team 1!

678
00:29:51,020 --> 00:29:52,155
I'm talking to you, Team 1!

679
00:29:52,380 --> 00:29:53,940
Hurry up, don't just stay there.

680
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,740
Let me take over. Take a break.

681
00:29:56,180 --> 00:29:57,540
Healers, heal! DPS, focus!

682
00:29:57,540 --> 00:29:58,820
What are you all staring at?

683
00:29:58,820 --> 00:30:00,300
Do you want a red-carpet welcome?

684
00:30:00,820 --> 00:30:01,500
I've had it.

685
00:30:01,500 --> 00:30:03,140
Not one player is doing their job.

686
00:30:03,260 --> 00:30:04,780
Know your positions!

687
00:30:04,780 --> 00:30:05,820
Get into your positions!

688
00:30:05,940 --> 00:30:06,860
Stop standing there!

689
00:30:06,860 --> 00:30:08,160
Does no one know their job?

690
00:30:14,940 --> 00:30:15,490
What?

691
00:30:15,490 --> 00:30:16,200
Come outside. Now.

692
00:30:16,300 --> 00:30:17,066
What's your problem?

693
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:17,780
Get upstairs.

694
00:30:17,780 --> 00:30:19,700
I told you, I'm busy today.
I'm not going.

695
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:21,020
Oh, so you just decide that

696
00:30:21,220 --> 00:30:22,380
like you rule the world?

697
00:30:23,020 --> 00:30:24,020
There's work at the cafe.

698
00:30:24,020 --> 00:30:25,290
We're dealing with the cafe first.

699
00:30:25,290 --> 00:30:25,770
Let's go.

700
00:30:25,780 --> 00:30:26,060
You...

701
00:30:26,177 --> 00:30:27,260
What has gotten into you?

702
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:28,500
I said I'm not going!

703
00:30:28,777 --> 00:30:30,460
Since when do you get to boss me around?

704
00:30:30,540 --> 00:30:31,940
Since you lost your conscience!

705
00:30:32,020 --> 00:30:32,860
Alright, sorry.

706
00:30:33,060 --> 00:30:33,860
Please calm down.

707
00:30:34,355 --> 00:30:35,820
I don't care who calls the shot here.

708
00:30:36,140 --> 00:30:37,020
But I promise you,

709
00:30:37,020 --> 00:30:38,100
I only need one hour.

710
00:30:38,340 --> 00:30:39,100
Once I finish up

711
00:30:39,100 --> 00:30:40,420
the work with him, I'll leave.

712
00:30:40,620 --> 00:30:41,100
Ms. Lin.

713
00:30:41,620 --> 00:30:42,900
You'd better stay out of this.

714
00:30:43,660 --> 00:30:44,420
Wang Hai, listen.

715
00:30:44,688 --> 00:30:46,088
You need to think about

716
00:30:46,155 --> 00:30:47,111
what really matters.

717
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:47,980
Now, get upstairs.

718
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:48,380
Move.

719
00:30:48,460 --> 00:30:49,940
I'm not going! Just go back!

720
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:50,540
- Let's go.
- What are you doing?

721
00:30:50,540 --> 00:30:51,420
- Go back!
- Stop it!

722
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:53,422
Who told you to come down?
Get back up there. Move.

723
00:30:53,500 --> 00:30:55,060
Why are you grabbing me? Grab him!

724
00:30:55,420 --> 00:30:56,620
He's acting so high and mighty.

725
00:30:56,620 --> 00:30:57,540
Take it out on him!

726
00:30:57,644 --> 00:30:59,500
I'm angry
because you're always making trouble!

727
00:30:59,620 --> 00:31:00,300
Get upstairs. Now.

728
00:31:01,060 --> 00:31:01,580
Go!

729
00:31:02,100 --> 00:31:02,620
Let's go!

730
00:31:03,660 --> 00:31:04,740
Fine!

731
00:31:04,940 --> 00:31:06,022
Stop pulling. I can walk.

732
00:31:06,140 --> 00:31:07,460
I'm done with this. I'm done.

733
00:31:10,780 --> 00:31:11,980
I'm sorry for the scene.

734
00:31:13,622 --> 00:31:14,777
It's fine. How about it?

735
00:31:15,060 --> 00:31:15,780
I'll head out.

736
00:31:15,780 --> 00:31:17,220
We're done for today anyway.

737
00:31:18,020 --> 00:31:18,660
And...

738
00:31:19,500 --> 00:31:20,380
read the lore book

739
00:31:20,380 --> 00:31:21,780
and get back to me tomorrow.

740
00:31:22,740 --> 00:31:23,500
Sorry, San Mei.

741
00:31:24,140 --> 00:31:25,020
You two need to

742
00:31:25,180 --> 00:31:26,620
sit down and talk this through.

743
00:31:26,630 --> 00:31:27,730
Whether online novels or gaming,

744
00:31:27,730 --> 00:31:28,900
you need to decide your path.

745
00:31:31,620 --> 00:31:32,300
I'll see you out.

746
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:41,700
I'm sorry.

747
00:31:42,820 --> 00:31:44,020
It was bound to happen.

748
00:31:44,460 --> 00:31:45,380
Better now than later.

749
00:31:47,020 --> 00:31:47,660
My ride's here.

750
00:31:47,860 --> 00:31:48,580
Head back inside.

751
00:32:25,220 --> 00:32:25,820
I'm so sorry.

752
00:32:27,620 --> 00:32:28,820
I'll have Er Jiu apologize.

753
00:32:33,100 --> 00:32:33,740
Stop playing.

754
00:32:34,460 --> 00:32:35,260
Go to bed.

755
00:32:35,580 --> 00:32:36,420
Forget the practice.

756
00:32:37,820 --> 00:32:38,580
I'm logging on.

757
00:32:39,420 --> 00:32:40,020
Wait.

758
00:32:40,580 --> 00:32:41,500
Let the DPS lead.

759
00:32:42,020 --> 00:32:42,844
Healers, stay back.

760
00:32:43,060 --> 00:32:44,300
Just focus on the heals.

761
00:32:56,860 --> 00:32:57,580
On your left.

762
00:33:53,100 --> 00:33:56,700
(4:35 AM)
(Zhou Mei: Just woke up.)

763
00:33:56,700 --> 00:33:59,500
(You left at 3:00 AM?)

764
00:34:13,660 --> 00:34:14,260
Hello.

765
00:34:25,820 --> 00:34:26,780
And you are?

766
00:34:27,540 --> 00:34:28,377
Where's He Han?

767
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:31,540
He's up. In the bedroom.

768
00:34:50,300 --> 00:34:51,380
That girl out there...

769
00:34:51,380 --> 00:34:52,540
Wait. It's not like that.

770
00:34:52,620 --> 00:34:54,420
That's Lin Zhanqiao's assistant.

771
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:57,660
You've taken
Lin Zhanqiao's assistant, too?

772
00:34:58,780 --> 00:34:59,940
Is this revenge against her?

773
00:35:00,420 --> 00:35:02,540
Stop talking nonsense. I said no.

774
00:35:03,100 --> 00:35:05,300
She had nowhere to stay.
I got her a room nearby.

775
00:35:05,300 --> 00:35:06,860
She asked to have breakfast

776
00:35:06,860 --> 00:35:07,740
and some advice.

777
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:08,700
That's it.

778
00:35:12,100 --> 00:35:13,820
Does Lin Zhanqiao know

779
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:17,820
that her assistant is here?

780
00:35:18,380 --> 00:35:19,620
If no one here talks,

781
00:35:19,644 --> 00:35:20,533
she won't find out.

782
00:35:21,420 --> 00:35:22,500
Sorry.

783
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:28,140
Am I interrupting?

784
00:35:28,300 --> 00:35:28,780
No.

785
00:35:29,020 --> 00:35:29,700
Ready to eat?

786
00:35:30,220 --> 00:35:30,580
Yes.

787
00:35:31,180 --> 00:35:32,460
Is your friend joining us?

788
00:35:32,660 --> 00:35:33,340
No, thanks.

789
00:35:33,500 --> 00:35:34,500
Get her some coffee.

790
00:35:34,620 --> 00:35:35,020
Thanks.

791
00:35:35,260 --> 00:35:35,580
Sure.

792
00:35:57,100 --> 00:35:57,620
He Han?

793
00:36:05,380 --> 00:36:05,900
Coming.

794
00:36:06,220 --> 00:36:07,060
Let's eat together.

795
00:36:07,820 --> 00:36:08,500
Shrimp dumplings.

796
00:36:10,740 --> 00:36:11,660
Zhangzhu, get dressed.

797
00:36:11,820 --> 00:36:12,711
See you at the office.

798
00:36:13,044 --> 00:36:14,711
- Ms. Lin, let me explain.
- Save it.

799
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:15,740
I'll go.

800
00:36:21,580 --> 00:36:22,340
Lin Zhanqiao!

801
00:36:24,780 --> 00:36:25,380
Sorry.

802
00:36:26,900 --> 00:36:27,340
Thanks.

803
00:36:36,500 --> 00:36:37,780
♪Watch my words come alive in bloom♪

804
00:36:37,780 --> 00:36:39,220
♪Unleash six states in a chain of blows♪

805
00:36:39,220 --> 00:36:40,380
♪See a genius born to soar♪

806
00:36:40,380 --> 00:36:41,940
♪Rising high where the wide skies glow♪

807
00:36:41,940 --> 00:36:43,060
♪If you can catch my shadow♪

808
00:36:43,060 --> 00:36:44,620
♪You can cross the world and roam free♪

809
00:36:44,620 --> 00:36:45,780
♪Your next stop in your heart♪

810
00:36:45,780 --> 00:36:47,340
♪Must be me at the top♪

811
00:36:47,460 --> 00:36:48,460
♪Neon lights glaring bright♪

812
00:36:48,460 --> 00:36:49,980
♪Lighting up every hidden place♪

813
00:36:50,180 --> 00:36:51,660
♪I once climbed rooftops all alone♪

814
00:36:51,940 --> 00:36:52,970
♪Searching for the stars above♪

815
00:36:52,980 --> 00:36:54,300
♪Until I saw your eyes aglow♪

816
00:36:54,300 --> 00:36:55,860
♪Shining through the city lights♪

817
00:36:55,860 --> 00:36:56,340
♪Then I knew♪

818
00:36:56,340 --> 00:36:57,020
♪This was me♪

819
00:36:57,020 --> 00:36:58,540
♪The legend I had chased all along♪

820
00:36:58,540 --> 00:36:59,460
♪Never Stop♪

821
00:36:59,540 --> 00:37:00,380
♪From the city streets♪

822
00:37:00,380 --> 00:37:03,540
♪From the sea of stars♪

823
00:37:03,700 --> 00:37:04,900
♪Never Stop♪

824
00:37:05,220 --> 00:37:06,860
You even came after my assistant.

825
00:37:08,860 --> 00:37:10,340
I thought you hated roommates.

826
00:37:10,620 --> 00:37:11,700
We're not living together.

827
00:37:11,780 --> 00:37:12,660
She's next door.

828
00:37:13,820 --> 00:37:16,130
Think about it. A young girl, homeless.

829
00:37:16,130 --> 00:37:17,420
She's pitiful, right?

830
00:37:19,820 --> 00:37:21,740
I was doing my good deed for the day

831
00:37:22,300 --> 00:37:23,020
anonymously.

832
00:37:23,020 --> 00:37:23,580
Noble, right?

833
00:37:24,755 --> 00:37:25,820
You paid for the hotel?

834
00:37:26,180 --> 00:37:27,220
Of course. She's a fan.

835
00:37:27,860 --> 00:37:28,740
Tell her to move out.

836
00:37:28,820 --> 00:37:29,740
I'll find her a place.

837
00:37:30,540 --> 00:37:31,100
Your place?

838
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:32,155
Isn't it the same?

839
00:37:32,380 --> 00:37:33,180
Very different.

840
00:37:33,580 --> 00:37:35,220
No. She's still
crashing with someone.

841
00:37:36,660 --> 00:37:38,500
I don't want you to influence her.

842
00:37:38,740 --> 00:37:40,500
I don't want her dad
to lecture me again.

843
00:37:41,420 --> 00:37:42,860
Besides, paying for her room?

844
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:44,600
People will get the wrong idea.

845
00:37:45,740 --> 00:37:47,300
I'll look after my own assistant.

846
00:37:47,660 --> 00:37:48,420
But thanks.

847
00:37:50,644 --> 00:37:51,360
Don't mention it.

848
00:37:51,540 --> 00:37:52,220
It was nothing.

849
00:37:52,820 --> 00:37:53,850
Glad that's cleared up.

850
00:37:53,850 --> 00:37:54,860
You want to be helpful?

851
00:37:55,500 --> 00:37:56,060
Here's a task.

852
00:37:56,580 --> 00:37:57,020
What?

853
00:37:57,740 --> 00:37:58,860
Didn't you want a challenge?

854
00:38:01,620 --> 00:38:02,900
Gu Yan sure isn't shy.

855
00:38:03,177 --> 00:38:04,900
He's asking for favors
like it's nothing.

856
00:38:05,260 --> 00:38:06,020
He's being polite.

857
00:38:06,620 --> 00:38:07,220
I'm not.

858
00:38:09,100 --> 00:38:09,940
Bring him to me.

859
00:38:10,577 --> 00:38:11,860
I'll coach him personally.

860
00:38:11,940 --> 00:38:12,660
Happy now?

861
00:38:18,100 --> 00:38:18,700
Pajamas?

862
00:38:18,700 --> 00:38:19,580
Hurry up and shoot!

863
00:38:19,711 --> 00:38:20,620
You're a grown man.

864
00:38:20,620 --> 00:38:22,420
Don't be sneaky about it.
Take it properly.

865
00:38:23,420 --> 00:38:24,100
Do a group shot.

866
00:38:24,380 --> 00:38:24,780
Okay.

867
00:38:25,140 --> 00:38:25,860
One, two, three.

868
00:38:28,620 --> 00:38:28,860
Here.

869
00:38:28,860 --> 00:38:30,380
- Thanks, Mr. He Han.
- Thank you.

870
00:38:30,380 --> 00:38:31,060
Okay, bye.

871
00:38:31,300 --> 00:38:32,220
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

872
00:38:34,940 --> 00:38:35,660
So cool.

873
00:38:42,020 --> 00:38:42,980
Mr. He Han.

874
00:38:44,060 --> 00:38:45,540
I cleared things up with your boss.

875
00:38:45,700 --> 00:38:46,340
Don't worry.

876
00:38:47,060 --> 00:38:48,180
Thank you, Mr. He Han.

877
00:38:48,500 --> 00:38:48,980
Phone.

878
00:38:50,100 --> 00:38:50,700
Phone?

879
00:38:52,700 --> 00:38:53,740
Take your 180 yuan back.

880
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:55,180
For what?

881
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:56,220
The room.

882
00:38:56,333 --> 00:38:58,355
You paid for seven days,
but you only stayed one.

883
00:38:58,420 --> 00:38:59,660
Here's the rest back.

884
00:38:59,980 --> 00:39:00,580
We're even.

885
00:39:02,300 --> 00:39:03,980
So, you're kicking me out?

886
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:04,900
Not me.

887
00:39:04,900 --> 00:39:06,500
Your boss wants you at her place.

888
00:39:06,620 --> 00:39:07,130
Personally,

889
00:39:07,130 --> 00:39:08,620
I think I'm the easier roommate.

890
00:39:08,644 --> 00:39:10,060
Dealing with someone that intense

891
00:39:10,060 --> 00:39:11,580
at work and at home

892
00:39:11,580 --> 00:39:12,700
will drive you nuts.

893
00:39:12,940 --> 00:39:14,200
Take care of yourself.

894
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:17,740
Thank you, Mr. He Han.

895
00:39:43,140 --> 00:39:43,540
Coming!

896
00:39:48,300 --> 00:39:48,660
Mom.

897
00:39:53,888 --> 00:39:54,533
I'll take that.

898
00:40:08,700 --> 00:40:09,540
About yesterday...

899
00:40:10,420 --> 00:40:11,530
Do you think

900
00:40:11,530 --> 00:40:12,980
I went too far?

901
00:40:14,380 --> 00:40:16,540
Did I embarrass you in front of

902
00:40:16,660 --> 00:40:17,380
your friends?

903
00:40:19,300 --> 00:40:19,780
No.

904
00:40:20,380 --> 00:40:21,020
It's my fault.

905
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:24,900
At your age,

906
00:40:25,420 --> 00:40:27,620
it's easy to lose your way.

907
00:40:28,580 --> 00:40:29,620
As a woman,

908
00:40:30,260 --> 00:40:31,380
you can't rely on looks

909
00:40:31,580 --> 00:40:33,020
to win over men.

910
00:40:34,180 --> 00:40:36,140
That only leads to misery.

911
00:40:36,940 --> 00:40:37,500
Remember that.

912
00:40:38,020 --> 00:40:39,420
The only thing

913
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:40,740
that outlasts beauty

914
00:40:41,340 --> 00:40:42,460
is your character.

915
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:45,540
I'll remember.

916
00:40:47,460 --> 00:40:48,460
Don't think

917
00:40:48,580 --> 00:40:49,740
I'm being too harsh.

918
00:40:50,820 --> 00:40:52,100
When you're my age,

919
00:40:52,620 --> 00:40:54,220
you'll understand.

920
00:41:05,300 --> 00:41:05,780
I know.

921
00:41:07,540 --> 00:41:08,260
Just remember,

922
00:41:08,660 --> 00:41:09,500
everything I do

923
00:41:09,980 --> 00:41:10,940
is for your own good.

924
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:13,860
I get it.

925
00:41:15,660 --> 00:41:16,580
I can tell.

926
00:41:17,580 --> 00:41:19,580
Those two men from the other day?

927
00:41:20,140 --> 00:41:20,900
They both like you.

928
00:41:22,780 --> 00:41:23,820
But all they see

929
00:41:24,140 --> 00:41:25,140
is your face.

930
00:41:26,860 --> 00:41:27,860
In my opinion,

931
00:41:28,140 --> 00:41:30,220
neither of them is right for you.

932
00:41:33,020 --> 00:41:34,420
That's why I'm not looking to date.

933
00:41:37,460 --> 00:41:38,100
Good.

934
00:41:39,100 --> 00:41:40,300
When you pick a partner,

935
00:41:40,940 --> 00:41:42,020
looks,

936
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:43,900
status,

937
00:41:44,660 --> 00:41:45,700
and money

938
00:41:46,300 --> 00:41:47,620
don't really matter.

939
00:41:48,300 --> 00:41:50,540
Look at their family background instead.

940
00:41:51,980 --> 00:41:52,540
Remember.

941
00:41:52,780 --> 00:41:53,900
You are a product

942
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:55,380
of your upbringing.

943
00:41:55,660 --> 00:41:56,620
That's a fact.

944
00:42:01,380 --> 00:42:01,740
Here.

945
00:42:02,620 --> 00:42:03,300
Finish this.

946
00:42:04,020 --> 00:42:04,820
I should get going.

947
00:42:05,500 --> 00:42:07,100
I have a calligraphy lesson to attend.

948
00:42:08,860 --> 00:42:10,060
I had my apple today.

949
00:42:37,933 --> 00:42:38,977
Close the door.

950
00:42:39,155 --> 00:42:39,733
It's okay.

951
00:42:39,822 --> 00:42:40,822
The elevator is here.

952
00:43:05,921 --> 00:43:07,041
(I've been thinking.)

953
00:43:08,321 --> 00:43:11,601
(Everyone's most comfortable level of intimacy)

954
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:19,691
(is probably different.)

955
00:43:20,691 --> 00:43:22,441
♪If the sky♪

956
00:43:22,951 --> 00:43:24,351
♪And the sea♪

957
00:43:24,891 --> 00:43:26,601
♪Turned upside down♪

958
00:43:28,161 --> 00:43:30,091
♪If a swimming fish♪

959
00:43:30,491 --> 00:43:33,881
♪Fell in love with a flying bird♪

960
00:43:35,651 --> 00:43:37,621
♪If back then♪

961
00:43:37,981 --> 00:43:42,391
♪We had never let go♪

962
00:43:42,991 --> 00:43:49,271
♪We wouldn't be lost in the crowd♪

963
00:43:50,391 --> 00:43:52,541
♪We met in a thirteenth month♪

964
00:43:52,541 --> 00:43:54,411
♪Held each other in a fifth season♪

965
00:43:54,591 --> 00:43:57,031
♪And found our way back whole♪

966
00:43:57,871 --> 00:44:00,041
♪So let this surging love♪

967
00:44:00,041 --> 00:44:04,471
♪Rise like tides that never fall♪

968
00:44:05,371 --> 00:44:07,551
♪If we're caught in a pouring rain♪

969
00:44:07,551 --> 00:44:08,641
♪That's alright♪

970
00:44:09,181 --> 00:44:09,931
♪If we're buried♪

971
00:44:09,931 --> 00:44:12,631
♪By passing years all the better♪

972
00:44:12,891 --> 00:44:15,071
♪At least we still can keep♪

973
00:44:15,251 --> 00:44:19,671
♪This one eternal photograph♪

974
00:44:35,431 --> 00:44:37,721
♪We're on misaligned tracks♪

975
00:44:37,721 --> 00:44:39,481
♪Running in opposite ways♪

976
00:44:39,601 --> 00:44:42,071
♪Searching all along the way♪

977
00:44:42,871 --> 00:44:45,031
♪For the fire of our younger hearts♪

978
00:44:45,221 --> 00:44:50,131
♪And the beauty lost in time♪

979
00:44:50,131 --> 00:44:53,651
♪This time don't lose each other again♪

980
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:54,861
♪Only after loss♪

981
00:44:54,861 --> 00:44:57,491
♪Do we learn what truly matters most♪

982
00:44:57,901 --> 00:45:00,261
♪In another time and space♪

983
00:45:00,261 --> 00:45:01,821
♪We'll stay and walk together♪

984
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:04,651
♪Till we grow old♪

985
00:45:05,611 --> 00:45:07,901
♪But still the sky will never♪

986
00:45:07,901 --> 00:45:10,571
♪Turn with the sea♪

987
00:45:13,091 --> 00:45:15,501
♪But still a swimming fish won't♪

988
00:45:15,501 --> 00:45:20,711
♪Fall in love with a flying bird♪
